title: Dave Liebman on the benefits of a formal jazz education
description:
In my interview for the Jazz Master summit, one of my questions started out asking him about the moment in his early learning where he remembered moments of improvement. His answer developed into his thoughts on the benefits of today's jazz student compared to his generation of learning from the opportunities and people you could find to teach you. 

To hear the full hour-long interview, go to www.JazzMasterSummit.com.
fulltitle: Dave Liebman on the benefits of a formal jazz education
